<TITLE> Bangladesh's swine flu victim 'recovering' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 21 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh's single confirmed swine flu patient is recovering with treatment, said health minister Dr AFM Ruhul Haque on Sunday. "The person is in quarantine so that others do not become infected." Haque said treatment was being supervised by IEDCR director Dr Mahmudur Rahman and the patient had almost recovered. The unnamed swine flu victim was found to be infected on return from the USA, the government announced last week. The person was diagnosed with the disease while entering Bangladesh. "We are taking all precautions. People have nothing to fear, but all must be aware," said Haque. The health minister was speaking at the conclusion of a two-day international conference of the Society of Laparoscopy Surgeons of Bangladesh at the Dhaka Sheraton. bdn
